properties.abstract: The largest and most wonderful alp in Switzerland is Urnerboden, where in summer up to 1200 cows graze. There is plenty of nostalgia, down-to-earth ambience, and you can enjoy the local produce like alpine cheese.
properties.description:
Having biked a short way on the Klausenpass road, you branch off on the nature trail which leads to the Wngi alp. 
The gradual ascent is comfortable and leads you along lush alpine meadows past the Orthalten alp to the Fiseten pass - at 2036 m above sea level the highest point of the tour - which is ideal for a rest. Enjoy the hard to beat panoramic views over Urnerboden, the Klausen pass, the Clariden glacier and the Glarus mountains, before you treat yourself to the downhill ride past the Gemsfairenhttli alp.

The next part again includes a climb: up to the Klausen pass at 1948 m above sea level. The view gets your heart pumping and the restaurant offers meal options in high alpine air. Next you bike along the historic Klausenpass road down the valley. Beneath Chlus you bike on the old military road, which winds itself along narrow zigzags through the gorge to Jgerbalm. The last part along the cool river Ftschbach is on an attractive single trail, all the way back to the starting point of Port.
